          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">Political crisis in Canada</h2>
        </mj-text>
         <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/gp-dec-19-1.jpg" alt="Political crisis in Canada" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau <a href="https://edition.cnn.com/2024/12/17/americas/justin-trudeau-donald-trump-canada-intl-hnk/index.html" target="_blank">faces</a> tremendous pressure to resign as his popularity diminishes due to economic issues and internal dissent within his Liberal Party. Trudeau‚Äôs leadership was questioned after Canada‚Äôs Finance Minister Chrystia Freeland resigned over disagreements on how Trudeau handled U.S. President-elect Donald Trump‚Äôs <a href="https://edition.cnn.com/2024/11/25/politics/trump-tariffs-mexico-canada-china/index.html" target="_blank">tariff threats</a>. She criticized Trudeau for putting political tactics (a 2-month <a href="https://www.cbsa-asfc.gc.ca/publications/cn-ad/cn24-43-eng.html" target="_blank">sales tax break</a> on holiday essentials and 250 Canadian dollar <a href="https://www.canada.ca/en/department-finance/news/2024/11/more-money-in-your-pocket-the-working-canadians-rebate.html" target="_blank">rebates</a> for workers) above fiscal responsibility, exposing some infighting within the Liberal Party.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Trudeau‚Äôs <a href="https://apnews.com/article/trudeau-canada-resign-freeland-trump-f346160f062846bbbaac73dbdd597941" target="_blank">options</a> include resigning, surviving a no-confidence vote, or clinging to power until the next election, likely in 2025. If Trudeau steps down, his potential successors could be Mark Carney, former head of the Bank of Canada, or Finance Minister Dominic LeBlanc. The opposition parties could put forth a no-confidence vote, forcing an early election where polls show the Conservatives hold a significant lead (43% to 23%).‚Äã</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
