          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Spy in disguise</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/gp-dec-19-2.jpg" alt="Spy in disguise" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Chinese businessman Yang Tengbo is <a href="https://www.france24.com/en/europe/20241217-chinese-businessman-yang-tengbo-links-uk-politics-royal-family-accused-espionage" target="_blank">banned</a> from entering the UK over allegations of espionage and ties to <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2024/dec/16/prince-andrew-to-miss-royal-family-christmas-after-links-to-alleged-chinese-spy-emerge" target="_blank">Prince Andrew</a>. Known in court as " H6,‚Äù Yang reportedly fostered links with British elites, including former Prime Ministers and royals, through ventures like <a href="https://pitchatpalace.com/" target="_blank">Pitch@Palace</a> China. Authorities claim Yang‚Äôs activities align with the Chinese Communist Party‚Äôs goals to influence foreign leaders, which the Home Office claimed ‚Äúcovert and deceptive.‚Äù</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Yang claims he is innocent of wrongdoing, arguing his actions were legitimate business endeavors and intends to appeal the ruling. His case highlights tensions in UK-China relations as PM Keir Starmer seeks closer economic ties with China while addressing security concerns. Critics like MP Ian Duncan-Smith <a href="https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cvg68vyz9lgo" target="_blank">label</a> Yang a symptom of broader Chinese influence efforts, though experts question their effectiveness and scale.‚Äã</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
