        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">HTS integration </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Murhaf Abu Qasra, the military chief of Syria's Islamist group, Hayat Tahrir Al-Sham (HTS),  announced that the group plans to <a href="https://www.arabnews.com/node/2583476/middle-east" target="_blank">dissolve</a> its armed wing and integrate into Syria's official armed forces. He emphasized that all military units should eventually be part of the national institution and that HTS would take the initiative. Abu Qasra called for the lifting of the "terrorist" designation on HTS and its leader, Ahmed Al-Sharaa (formally known as Abu Mohammed Al-Golan), who remains sanctioned by the US and other Western nations.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">HTS is trying to give itself a <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FUWYdZkt2Qk" target="_blank">moderate</a> facelift and pledges to protect religious and minority groups in areas under its control. <a href="https://www.dw.com/en/middle-east-german-delegation-meets-syrias-hts/live-71088507" target="_blank">Germany</a> and the <a href="https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/czd40pd1g7lo" target="_blank">UK</a> have started talks with the HTS leader. The European Union also <a href="https://www.aa.com.tr/en/europe/eu-to-reopen-delegation-in-syria-amid-renewed-diplomatic-push/3426751" target="_blank">announced</a> its intention to reopen its diplomatic representation in Damascus and is discussing dropping some sanctions on Syria.</p>
        </mj-text>
    </mj-section>

