          Diplomatic efforts for a Gaza <a href="https://edition.cnn.com/2024/12/17/middleeast/hamas-optimism-gaza-hostages-ceasefire-deal-intl-latam/index.html" target="_blank">ceasefire</a> show some developments as Hamas and international officials express optimism. Talks in Doha, involving Hamas, Israel, and mediators like Qatar, Egypt, and the US, are focusing on a deal pairing a hostage release with a ceasefire in phases. While challenges remain, including disagreements over Israeli troop presence, US officials are intensifying negotiations. Hamas is accusing Israel of imposing new conditions, which poses a hurdle in the talks. Amid this, Israeli strikes on Gaza continue, worsening humanitarian conditions in the region‚Äôs few operational hospitals.</p>
