          Several hundred North Korean troops have been <a href="https://www.euronews.com/my-europe/2024/12/18/hundreds-of-north-korean-troops-killed-fighting-for-russia-against-ukraine-says-us" target="_blank">killed</a> or injured while fighting for Russia against Ukraine, according to a senior US military official. The casualties are reportedly high due to the inexperienced soldiers, who are not battle-hardened. There are even some rumors that North Korean soldiers have <a href="https://www.newsweek.com/north-korea-troops-soldiers-killed-russia-language-barrier-2001452" target="_blank">accidentally</a> killed Russian soldiers over language barriers. North Korea sent approximately 10,000 troops to support Russian forces stationed in Russia's Kursk region to aid in attempts to recapture land lost to Ukraine in early August. In exchange for troops and military assistance, Moscow has been sending oil to North Korea.</p>
